definition: having nothing (idiom); utterly destitute/without two sticks to rub together
actually/place/classifier for houses, small buildings, institutions etc/that which/particle introducing a relative clause or passive/CL:個|个[ge4]
to have/there is/there are/to exist/to be

sentences.english: I want to confess as best I can, but my heart is void.
sentences.chinese: 我想要尽我所能地坦诚，然而我的心却空无所有。

sentences.english: Perhaps there is no one there.
sentences.chinese: 或许那里就是空无所有。
